      <p>The <a href="ch73s05.html#MonstersAnimals15">black bear</a> is a forest-dwelling omnivore that usually is not dangerous unless an interloper threatens its cubs or food supply.</p>
      <p><a href="ch73s05.html#MonstersAnimals15">Black bears</a> can be pure black, blond, or cinnamon in color and are rarely more than 5 feet long.</p>
